Jeff's got it right. I've got tools I've been using for 35+ years that were
made in .. well, who knows where?

The MAC and Snap-on guys stay in business by selling tools to mechanics that
work at shops and pay for them using the easy pay plan. They pay the driver
a little each week and essentially stay in debt to them for years.

